{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.4",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 4",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 4 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:1",
      "text": "Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:2",
      "text": "If we assay to commune with thee, wilt thou be grieved? but who can withhold himself from speaking?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:3",
      "text": "Behold, thou hast instructed many, and thou hast strengthened the weak hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:4",
      "text": "Thy words have upholden him that was falling, and thou hast strengthened the feeble knees.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:5",
      "text": "But now it is come upon thee, and thou faintest; it toucheth thee, and thou art troubled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:6",
      "text": "Is not this thy fear, thy confidence, thy hope, and the uprightness of thy ways?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:7",
      "text": "Remember, I pray thee, who ever perished, being innocent? or where were the righteous cut off?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:8",
      "text": "Even as I have seen, they that plow iniquity, and sow wickedness, reap the same.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:9",
      "text": "By the blast of God they perish, and by the breath of his nostrils are they consumed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:10",
      "text": "The roaring of the lion, and the voice of the fierce lion, and the teeth of the young lions, are broken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:11",
      "text": "The old lion perisheth for lack of prey, and the stout lion’s whelps are scattered abroad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:12",
      "text": "Now a thing was secretly brought to me, and mine ear received a little thereof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:13",
      "text": "In thoughts from the visions of the night, when deep sleep falleth on men,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:14",
      "text": "Fear came upon me, and trembling, which made all my bones to shake.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:15",
      "text": "Then a spirit passed before my face; the hair of my flesh stood up:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:16",
      "text": "It stood still, but I could not discern the form thereof: an image was before mine eyes, there was silence, and I heard a voice, saying,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:17",
      "text": "Shall mortal man be more just than God? shall a man be more pure than his maker?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:18",
      "text": "Behold, he put no trust in his servants; and his angels he charged with folly:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:19",
      "text": "How much less in them that dwell in houses of clay, whose foundation is in the dust, which are crushed before the moth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:20",
      "text": "They are destroyed from morning to evening: they perish for ever without any regarding it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.4.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 4:21",
      "text": "Doth not their excellency which is in them go away? they die, even without wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
